  "prompt": "Is it normal to be extremely motivated for few months and extremely depressed for few months?",
  "response": "What you're describing could be a sign of a mood disorder like Bipolar II Disorder, which involves cycles of depression and hypomania (elevated mood). However, only a qualified mental health professional can provide an accurate diagnosis. Some possibilities include:\n\n1. Bipolar Disorder\n- Alternating periods of high motivation and depression\n- Significant mood swings\n- Requires professional diagnosis and treatment\n\n2. Cyclical Depression\n- Seasonal Affective Disorder (SAD)\n- Periodic depressive episodes\n\n3. Other potential factors:\n- Stress\n- Burnout\n- Life changes\n- Hormonal imbalances\n- Underlying mental health conditions\n\nRecommendations:\n- Consult a mental health professional\n- Keep a mood journal\n- Practice consistent self-care\n- Maintain a stable routine\n- Consider therapy or counseling\n- Potential medication if diagnosed\n\nThese mood fluctuations can significantly impact your life, so seeking professional guidance is important for understanding and managing them effectively.\n\nWould you like to discuss this further or learn more about managing mood variations?",
